<node TEXT="Early and Late Binding (Visual Basic) 07/20/2015; 2 minutes to read +5; In this article. The Visual Basic compiler performs a process called binding when an object is assigned to an object variable. An object is early bound when it is assigned to a variable declared to be of a specific object type. Early bound objects allow the compiler to allocate memory and perform other optimizations before " ID="ID_1781315784" CREATED="1569323920145" MODIFIED="1569323920145"/>
</node>
