<node TEXT="Early vs. Late Binding . There are two ways to connect Excel with another application Early Binding and Late Binding. Early Binding sets the connections between Excel and the other application early in the process i.e. during design time. In Late Binding the connection isnt made until later during run time." ID="ID_149015020" CREATED="1569323920145" MODIFIED="1569323920145"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Early Binding vs. Late Binding - c-sharpcorner.com" ID="ID_424383491" CREATED="1569323920145" MODIFIED="1569323920145" LINK="https://www.c-sharpcorner.com/uploadfile/babu_2082/early-binding-vs-late-binding/">
<node TEXT="Early Binding vs. Late Binding Now coming into the picture&#x2026; Application will run faster in Early binding since no boxing or unboxing are done here. Easier to write the code in Early binding since the intellisense will be automatically populated; Minimal Errors in Early binding since the syntax is checked during the compile time itself." ID="ID_1438230507" CREATED="1569323920145" MODIFIED="1569323920145"/>
</node>
